</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwAQw">where <i id="mwAQ0">h</i> is <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Planck's_constant" title="Planck's constant" id="mwAQ4" class="mw-redirect">Planck's constant</a>, <span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt207" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\lambda"}}' id="mwAQ8"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \lambda }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>λ<!-- λ --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lambda }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b43d0ea3c9c025af1be9128e62a18fa74bedda2a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.355ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\lambda "/></span><span about="#mwt207">
</span> is the wavelength and <i id="mwARA">c</i> is the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Speed_of_light" title="Speed of light" id="mwARE">speed of light</a>. This is sometimes known as the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Planck–Einstein_equation" title="Planck–Einstein equation" id="mwARI" class="mw-redirect">Planck–Einstein equation</a>.<sup about="#mwt427" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-26" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-26"}}'><a href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#cite_note-26" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 26;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[26]</span></a></sup> In quantum theory (see <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./First_quantization" title="First quantization" id="mwARM">first quantization</a>) the energy of the photons is thus directly proportional to the frequency of the EMR wave.<sup about="#mwt425" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-27" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-27"}}'><a href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#cite_note-27" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 27;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[27]</span></a></sup></p>

<p id="mwARQ">Likewise, the momentum <i id="mwARU">p</i> of a photon is also proportional to its frequency and inversely proportional to its wavelength:</p>

<dl id="mwARY"><dd id="mwARc"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt211" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"p = { E \\over c } = { hf \\over c } = { h \\over \\lambda }. "}}' id="mwARg"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle p={E \over c}={hf \over c}={h \over \lambda }.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
