</span> is the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Permeability_(electromagnetism)" title="Permeability (electromagnetism)" id="mwAqA">permeability</a> of a vacuum (4<span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt544" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\pi"}}' id="mwAqE"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \pi }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \pi }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9be4ba0bb8df3af72e90a0535fabcc17431e540a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.332ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="\pi "/></span><span about="#mwt544">
</span> x 10<sup id="mwAqI">-7</sup> (<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Henry_(unit)" title="Henry (unit)" id="mwAqM">H</a>/m)), and <span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt546" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\varepsilon_0"}}' id="mwAqQ"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \varepsilon _{0}}">
  <semantics>
