<p id="mwAro">Evaluating the left hand side of (<b about="#mwt253" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"EquationNote","href":"./Template:EquationNote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"5"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwArs"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#math_5">5</a></b>) with the above identity and simplifying using (<b about="#mwt254" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"EquationNote","href":"./Template:EquationNote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"1"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwArw"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#math_1">1</a></b>), yields:</p>

