<p id="mwAsI">Combining (<b about="#mwt261" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"EquationNote","href":"./Template:EquationNote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"6"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAsM"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#math_6">6</a></b>) and (<b about="#mwt262" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"EquationNote","href":"./Template:EquationNote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"7"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAsQ"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#math_7">7</a></b>) again, gives a vector-valued <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Differential_equation" title="Differential equation" id="mwAsU">differential equation</a> for the electric field, solving the homogeneous Maxwell equations:</p>

<span about="#mwt264" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Equation box 1","href":"./Template:Equation_box_1"},"params":{"border":{"wt":"2"},"border color":{"wt":"#ccccff"},"equation":{"wt":"&lt;math>\\nabla^2 \\mathbf{E} = \\mu_0 \\varepsilon_0 \\frac{\\partial^2 \\mathbf{E}}{\\partial t^2}&lt;/math>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAsY">
