<p id="mwAsc">Taking the curl of the fourth Maxwell equation (<b about="#mwt265" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"EquationNote","href":"./Template:EquationNote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"4"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAsg"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#math_4">4</a></b>) results in a similar differential equation for a magnetic field solving the homogeneous Maxwell equations:</p>

<span about="#mwt267" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Equation box 1","href":"./Template:Equation_box_1"},"params":{"border":{"wt":"2"},"border color":{"wt":"#ccccff"},"equation":{"wt":"&lt;math>\\nabla^2 \\mathbf{B} = \\mu_0 \\varepsilon_0 \\frac{\\partial^2 \\mathbf{B}}{\\partial t^2}.&lt;/math>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAsk">
</span><dl about="#mwt267"><dd><table cellpadding="5" style="border:2px solid #50C878;background: #ECFCF4; text-align: center;">
<tbody><tr><td>
