ric effect, scattering.)"</span></li><li about="#cite_note-31" id="cite_note-31"><a href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#cite_ref-31" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-31" class="mw-reference-text">Browne, p 376: "Radiation is emitted or absorbed only when the electron jumps from one orbit to the other, and the frequency of radiation depends only upon on the energies of the electron in the initial and final orbits.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-32" id="cite_note-32"><a href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#cite_ref-32" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-32" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt94" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Spectroscopy"},"url":{"wt":"http://www.redshift.org.uk/spectroscopy"},"website":{"wt":"National Redshift Project"},"publisher":{"wt":"National Redshift Project"},"accessdate":{"wt":"19 January 2017"},"deadurl":{"wt":"no"},"archiveurl":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20170201234024/http://www.redshift.org.uk/spectroscopy"},"archivedate":{"wt":"1 February 2017"},"df":{"wt":"dmy-all"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBBg"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.redshift.org.uk/spectroscopy" id="mwBBk">"Spectroscopy"</a>. <i id="mwBBo">National Redshift Project</i>. National Redshift Project. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170201234024/http://www.redshift.org.uk/spectroscopy" id="mwBBs">Archived</a> from the original on 1 February 2017<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwBBw">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwBB0">19 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=National+Redshift+Project&amp;rft.atitle=Spectroscopy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.redshift.org.uk%2Fspectroscopy&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AElectromagnetic+radiation" class="Z3988" about="#mwt94" id="mwBB4"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt94" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBB8"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-HerschelRSIR-33" id="cite_note-HerschelRSIR-33"><a href="./Electromagnetic_radiation#cite_ref-HerschelRSIR_33-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-HerschelRSIR-33" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt106" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"jstor":{"wt":"107057"},"title":{"wt":"Experiments on the Refrangibility of the Invisible Rays of the Sun. By William Herschel, LL. D. F. R. S"},"first":{"wt":"William"},"last":{"wt":"Herschel"},"date":{"wt":"1 January 1800"},"journal":{"wt":"Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London"},"volume":{"wt":"90"},"pages":{"wt":"284–292"},"doi":{"wt":"10.1098/rstl.1800.0015"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBCA">Herschel, William (1 January 1800). "Experiments on the Refrangibility of the Invisible Rays of the Sun. By William Herschel, LL. D. F. R. S". <i id="mwBCE">Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London</i>. <b id="mwBCI">90</b>: 284–292. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwBCM">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1098%2Frstl.1800.0015" id="mwBCQ">10.1098/rstl.1800.0015</a>. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./JSTOR" title="JSTOR" id="mwBCU">JSTOR</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBCY"> </span><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//www.jstor.org/stable/107057" id="m